Host CPU -> AXI-Lite Interface -> Matrix Multiplication Accelerator
                          |-> Control Registers
                          |-> Input Buffer A
                          |-> Input Buffer B
                          |-> MAC Array / Multiply Core
                          |-> Accumulator
                          |-> Output Buffer
                          -> Result back to Host
###The system diagram shows a host processor communicating with the matrix multiplication chiplet through a standard AXI-Lite interface. Inside the chiplet, control logic, input buffers, a multiply-and-accumulate core, and an output buffer work together to perform the target kernel.
